cting these Lyman alpha spheres,\nwhich would be present at redshifts $z\\sim 30$ in the Cold Dark Matter model.\nTheir observation would represent a direct proof of the detection of a first\nstar.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 17 May 2006 23:04:07 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 24 Dec 2007 05:02:29 GMT"}],"update_date":"2010-11-11"}
